{
  "local_port": 48974,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to check your PF balance?",
  "response": "Checking your Provident Fund (PF) balance in India can be done through several methods. Here\u2019s a general procedure you can follow:\n\n1. **Using the Unified Member Portal:**\n   - Visit the official EPFO website and navigate to the unified member portal.\n   - Log in using your Universal Account Number (UAN), password, and captcha code.\n   - Once logged in, go to the 'View' section.\n   - Click on 'Passbook' to view your PF balance.\n\n2. **Using the UMANG App:**\n   - Download the UMANG app from your phone\u2019s app store.\n   - Register and log in using your mobile number.\n   - Select 'EPFO' from the app's list of services.\n   - Click on \u2018Employee Centric Services\u2019 and then on \u2018View Passbook.\u2019\n   - Enter your UAN and click on 'Get OTP.'\n   - Enter the OTP received on your registered mobile number to view your PF passbook.\n\n3. **Sending an SMS:**\n   - Ensure your UAN is linked with your KYC details.\n   - Send an SMS in the format: EPFOHO UAN ENG to 7738299899.\n   - You will receive your PF balance details via SMS in the preferred language (replace 'ENG' with the first three letters of your preferred language if different).\n\n4. **Using a Missed Call:**\n   - From your registered mobile number, give a missed call to 011-22901406.\n   - You will receive an SMS with your PF balance details.\n\n5. **Through your Employer's Portal:**\n   - Some employers provide access to a portal where you can check your PF details.\n   - Log in with your credentials and navigate to the PF section to view your balance.\n\nMake sure that your UAN is activated and linked with your mobile number and bank account for the above methods to work. If you experience issues, you may need to contact your employer's HR department or the nearest EPFO office for assistance.",
